<center><h2 style="font-family: 'Gochi Hand', cursive;">First Steps</h2></center>
<p style="font-family:'Architects Daughter', cursive;">  Today I learned about the Albertsons Companies and their strategic framework which includes a Goal, Identity, Strategic Priority, and Strategic Initiatives. I thought it was interesting to learn about the back end of what goes on in a grocery store and how complex it is. It was cool to learn about how Safeway got its name. The company was a safe way to shop for groceries during the Great Depression and prevent customers from going into any or more debt. They had a cash and carry operation to protect their customers.</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Architects Daughter', cursive;"> During the second portion of today’s class I learned about Web Apps and how they are made. I didn’t know how interconnected and complex web pages are. My main takeaway was that HTML(HyperText Markup Language) provides the basic structure of a web page; CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) changes the appearance of HTML so that we pages are easier to use and nicer to look at; and  JavaScript can manipulate HTML and CSSS to make web pages more reactive and dynamic. </p>
